CNA’s Motamed Says Pressure From Economy ‘Let Up’ on Insurers

-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 
2011-02-15T17:22:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/cna-s-motamed-says-pressure-from-economy-let-up-on-insurers.html
  CNA Financial Corp . Chief Executive
Officer Thomas Motamed, whose company is 90 percent-owned by  Loews Corp ., said the pressure of a weak economy on commercial
insurers is starting to “let up.”  Job cuts and plant closings have led business clients to
scale back coverage, Motamed said today during an investor
conference in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in New York at 
 nbuhayar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
